WEBVTT

00:06.674 --> 00:09.510
[♪ Tower of Power:
"I Got To Groove"]

00:09.510 --> 00:14.265
♪ ♪

00:14.265 --> 00:16.308
♪ I helped you
with your problems ♪

00:16.308 --> 00:17.977
♪ You ought to help me
with mine ♪

00:17.977 --> 00:20.813
♪ Whoa, I got to know,
I got to know ♪

00:20.813 --> 00:23.190
♪ Just give me
some kind of sign ♪

00:23.190 --> 00:25.276
♪ You want to be
a lady scholar ♪

00:25.276 --> 00:26.986
♪ You ought to know
what to say ♪

00:26.986 --> 00:29.697
♪ Whoa, I got to know,
I got to know ♪

00:29.697 --> 00:31.824
♪ We can't go on this way ♪

00:31.824 --> 00:36.495
♪ Any major fool
down on 42nd Street ♪

00:36.495 --> 00:38.706
♪ Will tell you
There's no way ♪

00:38.706 --> 00:41.542
♪ To beat the heat... ♪

00:41.542 --> 00:43.377
I've seen all these, right?

00:43.377 --> 00:46.130
[woman]
No. Some of these are new.

00:46.172 --> 00:47.757
♪ ♪

00:47.757 --> 00:49.759
Mm.

00:49.759 --> 00:52.178
♪ ♪

00:52.178 --> 00:53.721
I like him.

00:53.721 --> 00:54.972
How much is he?

00:54.972 --> 00:57.057
♪ I've got to know... ♪♪

00:57.057 --> 01:01.312
♪ ♪

01:01.312 --> 01:03.147
[indistinct chatter]

01:03.147 --> 01:06.150
[suspenseful music]

01:06.150 --> 01:13.157
♪ ♪

01:13.157 --> 01:17.203
Ms. Temple?
I'm Pam Bailey.

01:17.203 --> 01:19.997
This is Richard Lehmann
from the DC office.

01:19.997 --> 01:22.333
He will be overseeing
today's interview.

01:22.333 --> 01:25.669
- Shall we?
- Thank you.

01:25.669 --> 01:32.676
♪ ♪

01:34.762 --> 01:36.305
[Lehmann] Okay.

01:36.305 --> 01:39.016
So we've outlined
how you identified soldiers

01:39.016 --> 01:42.061
who met your desired profile.

01:42.061 --> 01:44.480
I'd like to go
back to the ingestion.

01:44.480 --> 01:46.023
[man]
All right.

01:46.023 --> 01:48.067
Your corporation was aware

01:48.067 --> 01:50.653
of the possibility of overdose.

01:50.653 --> 01:52.863
Overdose is always
a possibility.

01:52.863 --> 01:56.325
But the men were not informed
they were being medicated.

01:56.325 --> 01:58.702
[man] They did sign waivers,
accepting full responsibility--

01:58.702 --> 02:00.830
No. We lied.

02:00.830 --> 02:03.833
The protocol was unacceptable.

02:03.833 --> 02:07.044
What happened to them
after this, uh...

02:07.044 --> 02:08.921
Bergman incident?

02:08.921 --> 02:11.215
[Temple] The men?
[Bunda] Yeah.

02:11.215 --> 02:12.800
They completed the cycle.

02:12.800 --> 02:15.761
Cutting them off midstream
was too dangerous.

02:15.761 --> 02:18.514
And--and then?

02:19.849 --> 02:22.893
Most of them returned to active
duty without further symptoms.

02:22.893 --> 02:24.395
Wait.

02:24.395 --> 02:28.148
Are you claiming now
that the program worked?

02:28.148 --> 02:29.984
No, the program as Colin...

02:29.984 --> 02:34.655
as Mr. Belfast conceived it,
was unethical.

02:34.655 --> 02:38.492
- It was wrong.
- And after that...

02:38.492 --> 02:41.495
[dramatic music]

02:41.495 --> 02:43.455
♪ ♪

02:43.455 --> 02:45.165
Sorry.
I'm not sure what you're...

02:45.165 --> 02:48.419
Did any of the men
that you treated come forward

02:48.419 --> 02:51.380
with issues or complaints

02:51.380 --> 02:53.465
about what
had happened to them?

02:53.465 --> 02:57.261
♪ ♪

02:57.261 --> 02:59.263
No.

02:59.263 --> 03:01.307
Hmm.

03:01.307 --> 03:03.017
All right, we're good.

03:03.017 --> 03:05.144
[Lehmann] Wait. There is still
a significant amount

03:05.144 --> 03:06.478
of material to get through.

03:06.478 --> 03:07.897
I said we're done, Rich.

03:07.897 --> 03:10.900
It's time to move on.

03:10.900 --> 03:17.781
♪ ♪

03:40.721 --> 03:42.431
[sign beeps]

03:44.642 --> 03:46.644
[sighs]

03:49.897 --> 03:54.485
[sighs] Opportunity.
This is an opportunity.

03:54.485 --> 03:56.320
[sighs]

03:56.320 --> 03:59.323
[light piano music]

03:59.323 --> 04:04.536
♪ ♪

04:04.536 --> 04:06.538
[Leonard]
Come on in.

04:06.538 --> 04:09.500
[door creaks]

04:09.500 --> 04:11.168
Oh, I can come back if...

04:11.168 --> 04:13.337
- No, no, no, no. This is good.
- [door closes]

04:13.337 --> 04:15.881
Take a seat.

04:15.881 --> 04:17.174
What'd they say?

04:17.174 --> 04:18.384
At the DOD?

04:18.384 --> 04:19.468
Yeah.

04:19.468 --> 04:20.928
It went well.

04:20.928 --> 04:23.222
They appreciated
that we came to them.

04:23.222 --> 04:27.059
I think we might be okay.

04:27.059 --> 04:28.352
Well, all right.

04:28.352 --> 04:30.729
[chuckles]

04:30.729 --> 04:32.731
Good job.

04:35.651 --> 04:37.152
Now, this...

04:37.152 --> 04:40.072
it's a nine-grain mush.

04:40.072 --> 04:42.074
Mmm.

04:43.701 --> 04:45.035
There you go.

04:45.035 --> 04:46.745
- Thank you.
- Hey.

04:46.745 --> 04:48.247
It's not good or anything,

04:48.247 --> 04:50.708
but you won't be hungry
again for days.

04:50.708 --> 04:52.001
[chuckles]

04:56.588 --> 04:58.340
[clears throat]

04:58.340 --> 05:01.510
I was hoping
to show you, um...

05:01.510 --> 05:03.804
There's some ideas
that I've been working on.

05:05.389 --> 05:07.975
We're thinking too small
with the roller.

05:07.975 --> 05:10.769
We're missing opportunities.

05:10.769 --> 05:13.522
Uh, yeah, well, as far as...

05:13.522 --> 05:14.898
Sir, if you'll just look,

05:14.898 --> 05:16.400
we're keeping
ourselves in a box,

05:16.400 --> 05:17.985
an echo chamber.

05:17.985 --> 05:19.820
The roller
has potential far beyond

05:19.820 --> 05:21.363
our traditional audience of...

05:21.363 --> 05:22.698
Right. I get it.

05:24.450 --> 05:27.411
I've been using it myself.
It's more than stress relief.

05:27.411 --> 05:31.331
I can do things now
that I couldn't before.

05:31.331 --> 05:33.208
- Audrey.
- Yes.

05:36.045 --> 05:40.090
It's great work.
Very creative.

05:40.090 --> 05:42.051
But...

05:42.051 --> 05:45.054
We're not doing
the roller anymore.

05:45.054 --> 05:49.683
[scoffs]
W-what--what do you mean?

05:49.683 --> 05:51.185
We're not doing it.

05:51.185 --> 05:53.437
At all?

05:53.437 --> 05:54.521
Right.

05:56.398 --> 05:58.942
If this is because
of what Colin did,

05:58.942 --> 06:01.653
- I can promise you that...
- No, couple of rotten guys.

06:01.653 --> 06:03.155
- Just get 'em out?
- Yes, exactly.

06:03.155 --> 06:05.991
No, that's not gonna do it.

06:05.991 --> 06:08.285
That's like, uh...

06:08.285 --> 06:12.122
what's that movie
with the--the blue guy?

06:12.122 --> 06:15.918
He's got that--
that golden lantern,

06:15.918 --> 06:18.545
lamp, or whatever?

06:18.545 --> 06:21.215
Um, Aladdin.

06:21.215 --> 06:23.884
No, no, sorry.
No, it wasn't a lamp.

06:23.884 --> 06:26.720
It was a ring.
It was golden.

06:26.720 --> 06:27.721
Little blue guy.

06:27.721 --> 06:28.722
Oh
Lord of the Rings.

06:28.722 --> 06:30.182
Right, that one.

06:30.182 --> 06:34.520
So the little guy,
he's--he's got his ring,

06:34.520 --> 06:36.396
and it makes him feel good.

06:36.396 --> 06:38.273
He loves it.

06:38.273 --> 06:41.360
But it changes him, right?

06:41.360 --> 06:43.195
His eyes get really weird,

06:43.195 --> 06:47.116
and his skin turns,
and it's a bad scene.

06:47.116 --> 06:49.743
Every minute of every day,

06:49.743 --> 06:54.581
everything he does,
it's just for that ring.

06:54.581 --> 06:57.334
And he doesn't even realize it.
He thinks he's happy.

06:57.334 --> 07:01.213
[dramatic music]

07:01.213 --> 07:02.673
I'm sorry.
I don't...

07:02.673 --> 07:04.049
I thought we could make
people's lives

07:04.049 --> 07:07.052
just a little easier,
and then...

07:07.052 --> 07:10.514
[sighs]

07:10.514 --> 07:15.352
I've been out there every day.

07:15.352 --> 07:19.273
It's all I've been thinking
about for years.

07:19.273 --> 07:21.316
That's what it's done to me.

07:21.316 --> 07:23.694
And now look.

07:23.694 --> 07:25.154
Everything's gone,

07:25.154 --> 07:28.782
except for these
fucking things.

07:28.782 --> 07:32.411
And these guys,

07:32.411 --> 07:35.205
these...

07:35.205 --> 07:36.748
these soldiers...

07:36.748 --> 07:38.625
♪ ♪

07:38.625 --> 07:41.336
They were fucking eating it.

07:41.336 --> 07:43.714
You understand
what that can do to a person?

07:43.714 --> 07:46.633
So it's not on Belfast.
It's not on Ron.

07:46.633 --> 07:49.761
It's these precious berries.

07:49.761 --> 07:52.306
But we can't just throw
everything away.

07:52.306 --> 07:53.765
- Audrey...
- We are so close.

07:53.765 --> 07:56.393
In my opinion,
we can fix all of our mistakes.

07:56.393 --> 07:59.563
- None of that has to happen...
- Audrey, stop!

07:59.563 --> 08:02.024
♪ ♪

08:02.024 --> 08:05.027
Man, you need to learn
to read a room.

08:05.027 --> 08:07.863
I'm not interested
in your opinion.

08:07.863 --> 08:10.240
I said we're done.

08:10.240 --> 08:12.576
♪ ♪

08:12.576 --> 08:15.913
We make soap here, right?

08:15.913 --> 08:18.832
That's what we do.
We're gonna get back to it.

08:18.832 --> 08:23.128
♪ ♪

08:23.128 --> 08:25.589
[cell phone buzzing]

08:25.589 --> 08:28.050
[sighs]

08:28.050 --> 08:30.552
- You gonna take that?
- Uh, yes.

08:30.552 --> 08:32.429
[cell phone continues buzzing]

08:32.429 --> 08:34.723
♪ ♪

08:34.723 --> 08:35.724
This is Audrey Temple.

08:35.724 --> 08:37.476
Hi, it's Francine Bunda.

08:37.476 --> 08:39.019
We met briefly.

08:39.019 --> 08:40.604
Yes, hi.

08:40.604 --> 08:42.272
[Bunda]
I was wondering

08:42.272 --> 08:44.816
if I could get a tour
of your facility or whatever

08:44.816 --> 08:47.027
to see how
the hot dog gets made.

08:47.027 --> 08:49.613
Um, sure.
We could arrange that.

08:49.613 --> 08:52.991
Great.
Is now good?

08:52.991 --> 08:55.827
- Now?
- Yeah, I'm in the lobby.

08:55.827 --> 08:57.412
And--and bring Leonard.

08:57.412 --> 09:00.123
♪ ♪

09:00.123 --> 09:01.500
What?

09:01.500 --> 09:03.460
♪ ♪

09:03.460 --> 09:04.586
[sign beeps]

09:08.966 --> 09:10.259
Hi.

09:10.259 --> 09:11.593
Name and ID.

09:11.593 --> 09:15.889
[sighs]
Walter Cruz, 010168.

09:15.889 --> 09:17.891
I'm looking
for my medical records.

09:17.891 --> 09:19.393
There was an explosion, an IED,

09:19.393 --> 09:22.354
and I thought I had surgery,
so I just...

09:22.354 --> 09:24.731
Okay, one moment.

09:24.731 --> 09:27.734
[keys clacking]

09:29.069 --> 09:31.071
[sighs]

09:32.447 --> 09:34.074
[keys clacking]

09:34.074 --> 09:35.575
I'm not seeing that.

09:35.575 --> 09:36.702
- [Walter] What?
- Surgery.

09:36.702 --> 09:38.036
What do you mean?

09:38.036 --> 09:39.496
I was blown up,

09:39.496 --> 09:41.164
so they had
to have treated me, right?

09:41.164 --> 09:42.666
Oh, treatment.

09:43.875 --> 09:47.504
- One moment.
- [keys clacking]

09:47.504 --> 09:49.673
[sighs]

09:49.673 --> 09:51.675
I'm just saying, something
did happen to me, so...

09:51.675 --> 09:53.677
One moment.

09:53.677 --> 09:57.306
[keys clacking]

09:57.306 --> 09:59.725
Treatment.
Yes, I have that.

09:59.725 --> 10:01.852
Great.

10:01.852 --> 10:04.855
Administered
by Geist Emergent Group.

10:04.855 --> 10:06.023
That's a private contractor.

10:06.023 --> 10:09.026
So they did the surgery?

10:09.026 --> 10:12.571
- [keys clacking]
- [sighs]

10:12.571 --> 10:14.906
I'm not seeing that.

10:14.906 --> 10:17.534
Okay,
but they treated me, right?

10:17.534 --> 10:18.744
Yes.

10:18.744 --> 10:20.746
What kind of treatment?

10:20.746 --> 10:22.372
They're a private contractor.
I don't think I can...

10:22.372 --> 10:24.207
Sir, please step back.

10:24.207 --> 10:25.542
Well, you just told me Geist
did the treatment.

10:25.542 --> 10:27.127
I just want to know
what kind of treatment.

10:27.127 --> 10:29.713
Right, but we
didn't treat you there.

10:29.713 --> 10:31.089
That's a private contractor.

10:31.089 --> 10:32.549
What the fuck
does that mean, private?

10:32.549 --> 10:34.801
It wasn't us.
Outsourced.

10:34.801 --> 10:36.178
- Contract...
- But you have the information

10:36.178 --> 10:37.596
on your screen, okay?

10:37.596 --> 10:39.389
Why can't I just see it?

10:39.389 --> 10:41.391
I'm sorry.

10:43.852 --> 10:46.355
What the fuck
are you smiling about?

10:47.856 --> 10:49.066
I'm not.

10:49.066 --> 10:51.360
Look, all I'm asking...

10:52.944 --> 10:55.572
It was hard for me
to come down here, okay?

10:55.572 --> 10:58.367
There's no one I can...

10:58.367 --> 11:00.285
It's hard for me
to talk about this.

11:00.285 --> 11:02.371
You can understand that, right?

11:04.164 --> 11:07.876
I can submit a request
to the contractor.

11:07.876 --> 11:10.879
Great. Yeah, great.
Let's do that.

11:10.879 --> 11:13.757
[keys clacking]

11:13.757 --> 11:16.635
- Submitted.
- Okay.

11:16.635 --> 11:17.844
What do I do know?

11:17.844 --> 11:19.721
You wait.

11:19.721 --> 11:21.139
What, like,
get another number?

11:21.139 --> 11:22.891
Um, no.

11:22.891 --> 11:25.435
They'll get back to us
in eight to 12 weeks.

11:26.436 --> 11:27.896
Eight to 12 weeks?

11:27.896 --> 11:30.023
Well, officially.
Sometimes it's longer.

11:30.023 --> 11:31.900
Longer than 12 weeks?

11:31.900 --> 11:33.276
Just to tell me
what you already know.

11:33.276 --> 11:34.486
I'm losing
my fucking mind here!

11:34.486 --> 11:36.071
Sir, I need you to calm down.

11:36.071 --> 11:37.656
Why can't you tell me
what's on that screen?

11:37.656 --> 11:39.991
Because it's private.

11:39.991 --> 11:42.994
[exhales sharply]
Private.

11:42.994 --> 11:44.371
[sighs]

11:44.371 --> 11:45.622
Sure.

11:47.999 --> 11:49.459
Sir!

11:49.459 --> 11:53.296
[Bunda] Wow, well, thank you
so much for taking the time.

11:53.296 --> 11:56.174
This is quite a spread
you've got here.

11:56.174 --> 11:58.343
[Leonard] That's all jojoba.
[Bunda] Uh-huh.

11:58.343 --> 12:00.887
That's a great crop.
Lot of--lot of uses.

12:00.887 --> 12:02.431
Oh, that's fascinating.

12:02.431 --> 12:05.016
- Mm. Eh, people call it
a goat nut.

12:05.016 --> 12:06.435
Uh-huh.

12:06.435 --> 12:09.855
Because it's supposed
to look like goat testicles.

12:09.855 --> 12:11.731
- Hmm.
- I checked. It's true.

12:11.731 --> 12:14.901
Oh, well, of course you did.

12:14.901 --> 12:16.319
Huh?

12:16.319 --> 12:18.196
Oh...

12:18.196 --> 12:21.116
[Bunda] Oh, uh, excuse me,
is that, uh...

12:21.116 --> 12:22.742
Can we stop here?

12:22.742 --> 12:24.744
- Can we--can we stop here?
- Down here, sure.

12:24.744 --> 12:25.745
- Yeah.
- Thank you.

12:32.210 --> 12:33.837
[Bunda]
Oh, wow.

12:35.130 --> 12:39.217
So these are all the berries.

12:39.217 --> 12:40.635
[Leonard]
Yeah, for now.

12:40.635 --> 12:42.971
Soon, this will all be
ground cover.

12:42.971 --> 12:44.347
What do you mean?

12:44.347 --> 12:46.224
Well, once we get
the berries out,

12:46.224 --> 12:48.059
we got to give the soil
a chance to breathe.

12:48.059 --> 12:49.978
What--what do you mean,
get them out?

12:49.978 --> 12:52.564
We don't need them anymore.

12:52.564 --> 12:55.942
Came to our senses,
thanks to her.

12:55.942 --> 12:57.486
Huh.

12:59.404 --> 13:01.990
Well, I hate to be
a difficult guest,

13:01.990 --> 13:04.367
but I can't let you do that.

13:05.702 --> 13:07.829
What does that mean--
let me?

13:07.829 --> 13:10.582
Well, this is awkward.
I thought I had good news.

13:10.582 --> 13:12.584
We want to partner with you.

13:12.584 --> 13:14.127
[Audrey] Who? The...
- Pentagon.

13:14.127 --> 13:16.546
Yeah, we want as much
of this as possible

13:16.546 --> 13:18.298
as fast as possible.

13:18.298 --> 13:19.883
I don't understand.
You're saying...

13:19.883 --> 13:22.427
Well, you were very clear
in your presentation.

13:22.427 --> 13:25.764
The problem was the protocol,
the implementation.

13:25.764 --> 13:26.973
The substance itself was...

13:26.973 --> 13:28.183
Well, yes, but...

13:28.183 --> 13:30.727
The men that finished
the program,

13:30.727 --> 13:32.395
it helped them--
isn't that what you said?

13:32.395 --> 13:34.564
- No, I just...
- No, the whole fucking thing--

13:34.564 --> 13:37.067
what we did,
no good can come of that.

13:37.067 --> 13:39.110
Well, I just totally disagree.

13:39.110 --> 13:40.862
I think you were
way out over your skis.

13:40.862 --> 13:42.280
Mistakes were made.

13:42.280 --> 13:46.201
My people,
we do this work every day.

13:46.201 --> 13:48.620
All you're asking for
is just the extract.

13:48.620 --> 13:50.080
That's what you'd need.

13:50.080 --> 13:52.958
- [Bunda] Yes.
- Audrey.

13:52.958 --> 13:55.585
Now, we can't help you.

13:55.585 --> 13:57.837
You'd be compensated.

13:57.837 --> 13:59.297
Like, out the ass.

14:00.549 --> 14:01.883
You're not listening to me.

14:01.883 --> 14:05.470
Well, I think you're not
listening to me.

14:05.470 --> 14:08.431
Do you have a time machine?

14:08.431 --> 14:10.392
- A what?
- Any of these plants--

14:10.392 --> 14:11.643
if you eat them,

14:11.643 --> 14:13.436
will they
send you back in time?

14:13.436 --> 14:15.522
- No.
- Well, then the toothpaste

14:15.522 --> 14:17.274
is out of the tube, Leonard.

14:17.274 --> 14:20.485
You can't go back
and un-plant this plant.

14:20.485 --> 14:21.736
This is happening.

14:21.736 --> 14:24.447
[dramatic music]

14:24.447 --> 14:26.449
[chuckles]

14:26.449 --> 14:29.202
♪ ♪

14:29.202 --> 14:32.956
Audrey, would you mind
finishing the tour?

14:32.956 --> 14:36.126
Um, no, of course not.

14:36.126 --> 14:39.129
- Enjoy the rest of your day.
- You too.

14:39.129 --> 14:46.136
♪ ♪

14:46.136 --> 14:49.472
[gear shifter clacks,
cart rumbles]

14:49.472 --> 14:56.438
♪ ♪

15:00.817 --> 15:02.944
He's a funny old goat,
isn't he?

15:02.944 --> 15:04.321
I think he was just surprised.

15:04.321 --> 15:05.530
I'm pretty sure
he didn't mean it.

15:05.530 --> 15:07.324
Hey, listen,
forget about him.

15:07.324 --> 15:10.577
This is all
critical military technology.

15:10.577 --> 15:13.330
We need it,
which means it's ours.

15:13.330 --> 15:14.623
What about you?

15:14.623 --> 15:18.793
You know all about this,
the plant, the juice.

15:18.793 --> 15:21.171
Well, yes, but...

15:21.171 --> 15:24.799
All we need is someone
to help make it happen,

15:24.799 --> 15:28.678
someone with ideas
and solutions,

15:28.678 --> 15:30.930
with some fucking competence.

15:30.930 --> 15:32.349
But Leonard
seems pretty opposed.

15:32.349 --> 15:33.892
Look, I get it.

15:33.892 --> 15:36.186
You've done all the work,
and these guys come

15:36.186 --> 15:39.397
and take it from you
and fuck everything up.

15:39.397 --> 15:41.733
♪ ♪

15:41.733 --> 15:43.860
Well, I don't do fuck-ups.

15:43.860 --> 15:46.029
We're gonna get
this thing going.

15:46.029 --> 15:47.989
♪ ♪

15:47.989 --> 15:50.867
Okay, again,
tell me what she said,

15:50.867 --> 15:52.786
her exact words.

15:52.786 --> 15:53.828
[sighs]

15:53.828 --> 15:55.121
"All I need is someone

15:55.121 --> 15:58.291
who knows how to grow it,
pick it, and ship it."

15:58.291 --> 16:00.377
That's you.
You've done all that.

16:00.377 --> 16:02.128
I was Colin's assistant.
I wasn't...

16:02.128 --> 16:04.673
Colin spent half of his life

16:04.673 --> 16:06.299
in the Delta One Sky Lounge

16:06.299 --> 16:08.343
trying to get
a fucking upgrade.

16:08.343 --> 16:10.345
- I know.
- Meanwhile, you were the one

16:10.345 --> 16:12.514
overseeing production,
start to finish, right?

16:12.514 --> 16:13.848
Yeah.

16:13.848 --> 16:15.850
You said
you wanted to matter there.

16:15.850 --> 16:17.477
I do.

16:17.477 --> 16:19.479
Leonard is not
gonna listen to you.

16:19.479 --> 16:21.189
He's too much like Colin.

16:21.189 --> 16:22.649
- Bunda...
- Boo-nda.

16:22.649 --> 16:24.317
Okay, well,
whatever her name is,

16:24.317 --> 16:25.485
she believes in you.

16:25.485 --> 16:26.861
She sees something in you.

16:26.861 --> 16:27.987
But what if she's wrong?

16:27.987 --> 16:31.074
You inherited a mess, Temple.

16:31.074 --> 16:33.284
And you're gonna get
things back on track.

16:33.284 --> 16:35.537
You're gonna take a fucking
criminal investigation,

16:35.537 --> 16:38.623
and turn it
into a gigantic new contract,

16:38.623 --> 16:41.501
a whole new business model.

16:41.501 --> 16:42.877
So have a sip of that wine

16:42.877 --> 16:44.796
and think about that
for a second.

16:44.796 --> 16:47.799
[indistinct chatter]

16:47.799 --> 16:50.218
Hmm...

16:50.218 --> 16:53.221
[indistinct chatter continues]

16:59.477 --> 17:01.271
Maybe you're right.

17:01.271 --> 17:03.481
Of course, I'm right.

17:03.481 --> 17:05.734
[chuckles]

17:05.734 --> 17:07.777
Let's order some champagne.

17:07.777 --> 17:09.738
[snaps fingers]
That's what I'm talking about.

17:09.738 --> 17:12.282
- Garçon.
- Oh, God, Alex.

17:12.282 --> 17:13.283
Shut up.
He likes it.

17:13.283 --> 17:14.826
- Hi.
- Yes, hi.

17:14.826 --> 17:18.288
Um, we would like to order
some champagne, please.

17:18.288 --> 17:20.123
All right.
Do you have any preference?

17:20.123 --> 17:23.877
I want you to pick,
and I want to be astounded.

17:23.877 --> 17:26.921
I'll do my best.

17:26.921 --> 17:29.758
[laughs]

17:29.758 --> 17:33.595
I'll tell you one thing--
I'm gonna take Colin's office.

17:33.595 --> 17:36.473
Do it.
You are so legit right now.

17:36.473 --> 17:38.349
This is your moment.

17:39.976 --> 17:42.145
Right.

17:42.145 --> 17:45.231
Okay, what?

17:45.231 --> 17:48.526
Things aren't done.
They're still...

17:48.526 --> 17:50.695
Of course.
I was just saying

17:50.695 --> 17:53.907
if this works out...
when this works out...

17:53.907 --> 17:55.408
- Mm-hmm.
- We had talked about...

17:55.408 --> 17:58.369
- The baby idea.
- Yes.

17:58.369 --> 18:01.289
I went to go look
at donors today.

18:01.289 --> 18:04.209
And I found some really cool
Vietnamese guys,

18:04.209 --> 18:06.336
some great options.

18:06.336 --> 18:08.296
So she can be just like us.

18:08.296 --> 18:10.048
Sorry, who is she?

18:10.048 --> 18:11.716
The baby.

18:11.716 --> 18:12.801
Olive.

18:12.801 --> 18:14.969
Olive?

18:14.969 --> 18:16.763
It's open to discussion,
obviously.

18:16.763 --> 18:18.556
I just...

18:18.556 --> 18:20.558
I just thought it was cute.

18:22.268 --> 18:25.772
Alex, I'm gonna be crazy busy
if all of this happens.

18:25.772 --> 18:27.482
- How am I supposed to...
- I'll carry.

18:27.482 --> 18:29.776
- Don't worry.
- What about your job?

18:29.776 --> 18:31.194
I'll work up
until I can't anymore,

18:31.194 --> 18:32.445
and I'll take off a few weeks.

18:32.445 --> 18:34.405
Weeks?
That's nothing.

18:34.405 --> 18:36.491
Okay, months.
Three months, six months.

18:36.491 --> 18:38.451
I'll do whatever it takes.

18:40.161 --> 18:42.914
I know you don't believe
things are gonna work out,

18:42.914 --> 18:44.457
- but I promise you...
- You can't.

18:44.457 --> 18:45.875
Temple,
every day I go into work,

18:45.875 --> 18:48.253
I deal
with the shittiest of people,

18:48.253 --> 18:50.004
the lowest of low behavior.

18:50.004 --> 18:52.382
I swim in it.

18:52.382 --> 18:55.260
If something were to happen,
I know how to protect us.

18:57.637 --> 18:58.680
What if...

18:58.680 --> 19:00.807
What if?
What if what?

19:02.433 --> 19:05.186
Okay, prepare to be astounded.

19:05.186 --> 19:07.188
[cork pops]

19:07.188 --> 19:10.191
[dramatic music]

19:10.191 --> 19:12.193
♪ ♪

19:12.193 --> 19:15.196
[snoring]

19:15.196 --> 19:22.203
♪ ♪

19:46.686 --> 19:47.687
[Temple]
What?

19:50.148 --> 19:51.608
Mm?

19:51.608 --> 19:55.278
Walter Cruz
is requesting his records.

19:55.278 --> 19:58.907
- [Alex] Who?
- From Homecoming.

19:58.907 --> 20:01.367
- He emailed you?
- No, it's VA Compliance.

20:01.367 --> 20:04.704
- That all goes through me now.
- What does he want to know?

20:04.704 --> 20:07.040
I have no idea.
It doesn't say.

20:07.040 --> 20:08.499
Let me see it.

20:08.499 --> 20:11.502
[ominous music]

20:11.502 --> 20:13.338
♪ ♪

20:13.338 --> 20:14.923
This is nothing.

20:14.923 --> 20:16.716
Looks like it's
from some computer.

20:16.716 --> 20:18.718
They probably
won't even follow up.

20:18.718 --> 20:20.303
[sighs]

20:20.303 --> 20:21.763
Temple,
it's 5:00 in the morning.

20:21.763 --> 20:23.723
So go back to sleep.

20:23.723 --> 20:28.436
♪ ♪

20:28.436 --> 20:29.729
Fine.

20:29.729 --> 20:31.898
I'll call my guy.

20:31.898 --> 20:35.318
♪ ♪

20:35.318 --> 20:36.611
[sighs]

20:37.654 --> 20:39.948
Okay, was that before...

20:39.948 --> 20:41.991
Yeah.

20:41.991 --> 20:43.534
What was he asking?

20:43.534 --> 20:45.453
♪ ♪

20:45.453 --> 20:46.955
He's where?

20:46.955 --> 20:52.460
♪ ♪

20:52.460 --> 20:54.337
Is this in the same town?

20:54.337 --> 20:57.715
♪ ♪

20:57.715 --> 20:59.759
Okay.

20:59.759 --> 21:02.470
Thank you, Gary.
Good work.

21:02.470 --> 21:04.347
Bye.

21:04.347 --> 21:06.349
What?

21:07.809 --> 21:11.479
So this doesn't
actually change anything...

21:11.479 --> 21:14.691
- Alex, just tell me.
- [sighs]

21:14.691 --> 21:16.150
Walter Cruz is in jail.

21:16.150 --> 21:17.735
There was an incident
at a VA office.

21:17.735 --> 21:19.529
He's in jail?

21:19.529 --> 21:22.156
Yes.

21:22.156 --> 21:24.450
I need...I'm gonna go in.

21:24.450 --> 21:26.285
I-I'm gonna...
I just need to call.

21:26.285 --> 21:27.495
Who--who do you have to call?

21:27.495 --> 21:29.247
Bunda.

21:29.247 --> 21:31.249
- Why?
- Because, Alex,

21:31.249 --> 21:33.501
she asked me specifically
if any clients

21:33.501 --> 21:35.962
had come forward with an issue,
and I said, "No."

21:35.962 --> 21:37.630
Yeah, but you were
telling her the truth

21:37.630 --> 21:40.591
Not anymore.

21:40.591 --> 21:42.385
Okay,
and then what did she say?

21:42.385 --> 21:44.137
[Temple scoffs]
What?

21:44.137 --> 21:45.138
What was her response?

21:45.138 --> 21:46.764
She said...

21:46.764 --> 21:49.767
"We're done.
It's time to move on."

21:51.019 --> 21:53.646
[sighs]

21:53.646 --> 21:55.606
- What?
- You need to listen to people

21:55.606 --> 21:56.858
when they're trying
to tell you something.

21:56.858 --> 21:58.526
What was she trying to tell me?

21:58.526 --> 22:00.653
[Alex]
She's restarting the program.

22:00.653 --> 22:02.989
She needs the past to go away.

22:02.989 --> 22:05.700
She was trying to tell you
that you need to handle it.

22:05.700 --> 22:07.744
She's taking care of Geist,

22:07.744 --> 22:09.454
and she wants you
to take care of things

22:09.454 --> 22:11.080
like this Walter situation.

22:11.080 --> 22:13.291
That's what
she was trying to tell me?

22:13.291 --> 22:16.252
- You're sure?
- Yes, 100%.

22:17.628 --> 22:19.255
This is exactly
what I was afraid of.

22:19.255 --> 22:20.590
Nothing is stable.

22:20.590 --> 22:22.508
Okay, nobody is talking
about the fucking baby.

22:22.508 --> 22:24.052
I am!

22:35.188 --> 22:38.191
[upbeat music]

22:38.191 --> 22:42.320
♪ ♪

22:42.320 --> 22:44.280
I'll take care of it.

22:44.280 --> 22:47.283
[Temple] What does that mean?
[Alex] I'll go talk to him.

22:47.283 --> 22:49.160
You're just gonna
call him up, say,

22:49.160 --> 22:52.497
"Hi. The Geist Emergent Group
has a couple of questions."

22:52.497 --> 22:54.165
Of course not.

22:54.165 --> 22:55.458
You don't understand my job.

22:55.458 --> 22:56.709
You're a crisis manager,
not a...

22:56.709 --> 22:58.086
[Alex]
No, I perform.

22:58.086 --> 23:00.213
He just needs
someone to talk to,

23:00.213 --> 23:02.006
and I'll be that person.

23:02.006 --> 23:03.925
Alex, he's not a lawyer
who pulled out his wiener

23:03.925 --> 23:05.843
at a Christmas party--
he's a soldier.

23:05.843 --> 23:09.263
I know that,
and I've handled that before.

23:09.263 --> 23:11.182
[Temple] What we did to him
is real. We can't...

23:11.182 --> 23:13.309
[Alex] If we stop him now,
at least we get to feel

23:13.309 --> 23:15.103
like he's making
his own decision.

23:15.103 --> 23:18.189
Or we let him
keep running with this,

23:18.189 --> 23:20.858
and he gets himself
into real trouble.

23:20.858 --> 23:22.485
We're giving him an out.

23:22.485 --> 23:29.492
♪ ♪

23:31.410 --> 23:32.703
What's that for?

23:32.703 --> 23:34.330
Contingencies.

23:34.330 --> 23:36.707
♪ ♪

23:38.918 --> 23:41.212
- Give me that.
- What?

23:41.212 --> 23:44.340
This. You don't need it.
You're stronger than that.

23:47.135 --> 23:48.803
I'll be back soon.

23:50.346 --> 23:52.515
Okay.

23:52.515 --> 23:53.724
I love you.

23:56.352 --> 23:58.354
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

24:08.531 --> 24:11.534
[keys clacking]

24:11.534 --> 24:14.537
[dramatic music]

24:14.537 --> 24:21.544
♪ ♪

25:27.235 --> 25:30.238
[music swelling]

25:30.238 --> 25:36.994
♪ ♪

25:36.994 --> 25:38.996
[music stops]

25:40.873 --> 25:42.416
[indistinct chatter]

25:42.416 --> 25:44.126
[Alex] Hi.
- Yeah.

25:44.126 --> 25:46.128
Do you have a Walter Cruz here?

25:46.128 --> 25:47.630
You his girlfriend?

25:49.048 --> 25:51.050
I'm here to bail him out.

25:54.262 --> 25:55.846
Thank you.

26:01.060 --> 26:03.646
[indistinct PA announcement]

26:03.646 --> 26:06.065
[telephone ringing]

26:07.650 --> 26:10.653
[indistinct chatter
over radio]

26:39.098 --> 26:43.311
[door opens, closes]

26:46.314 --> 26:47.898
[man]
I'll let him know.

26:52.528 --> 26:55.531
[telephone ringing]

27:04.123 --> 27:07.126
[indistinct chatter]

28:26.497 --> 28:28.457
[computer beeps,
keys clacking]
